Reasoning: The paper deals with defining and modeling the relation of inclusion between continuous belief functions, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of normal distributions to simulate and analyze these relations suggests a connection to statistical inference (cs.SI) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the study of consonant belief functions may also relate to data structures (cs.DS).
